                                <h5 id="civility" class="faq-question"> <span class="faq-q">Q:</span>
                                    How is civility defined and determined?
                                </h5>
                                <h5 class="faq-answer">
                                    We will rely on a combination of algorithmic and human intervention based methods to ensure the civility of the platform. For users contemplating whether or not a line of argument will be considered uncivil, we recommend the "grandma test". If you would be uncomfortable making the argument in front of your grandma, it is probably not appropriate. <br> <br>
                                    Additionally, we take considerable inspiration from Paul Graham of Y Combinator, and for readers seeking to better understand the ethos we are striving for, please have a quick read of Paul's essay on <a href="http://paulgraham.com/disagree.html"> How to disagree</a> from 2008.
                                </h5>
                                <p class="faq-text">
                                </p>
